"title": "1652: numbers, 3–5",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "1652",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The number three, primarily associated with the doctrine of the Trinity, is also associated with periods of specially significant divine activity (e.g., “on the third day”). Four and five have a variety of associations.</p>\n<h2>Three</h2>\n<h3>The Trinity</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:19\">MAT 28:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:26\">JHN 14:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:26\">JHN 15:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:4-1Cor12:6\">1CO 12:4–12:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:2\">1PE 1:2</a></p>\n<h3>The triad of faith, hope and love</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor13:13\">1CO 13:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess1:3\">1TH 1:3</a></p>\n<h3>Three days</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen30:36\">GEN 30:36</a></strong> <em>Three days is a common period, often indicating the length of a journey or a period leading to a critical point.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen40:12-Gen40:22\">GEN 40:12–40:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:18\">EXO 3:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod10:22\">EXO 10:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num10:33\">NUM 10:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg14:14\">JDG 14:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs12:5\">1KI 12:5</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr10:5\">2CH 10:5</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ was raised after three days</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:46\">LUK 24:46</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:21\">MAT 16:21</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:31\">MRK 8:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:22\">LUK 9:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:23\">MAT 17:23</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:31\">MRK 9:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:19\">MAT 20:19</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:34\">MRK 10:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:33\">LUK 18:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:63-Matt27:64\">MAT 27:63–27:64</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:7\">LUK 24:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:21\">LUK 24:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:40\">ACT 10:40</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:3-1Cor15:4\">1CO 15:3–15:4</a>JON <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:17\">1:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:39-Matt12:40\">MAT 12:39–12:40</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:29-Luke11:30\">LUK 11:29–11:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:4\">MAT 16:4</a></p>\n<h3>Three brothers</h3>\n<p>Shem, Ham and Japheth:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen6:10\">GEN 6:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen7:13\">GEN 7:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen9:19\">GEN 9:19</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:21\">1SA 2:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam31:6\">1SA 31:6</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr10:6\">1CH 10:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam2:18\">2SA 2:18</a></p>\n<h3>Groups of three men</h3>\n<p>Job's friends:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job2:11\">JOB 2:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job32:3\">JOB 32:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job32:5\">JOB 32:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:1\">MAT 17:1</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:2\">MRK 9:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:28\">LUK 9:28</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:37\">MAT 26:37</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:33\">MRK 14:33</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen18:2\">GEN 18:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek14:14-Ezek14:18\">EZK 14:14–14:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan3:23-Dan3:24\">DAN 3:23–3:24</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech11:8\">ZEC 11:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam23:8-2Sam23:12\">2SA 23:8–23:12</a> <em>the Three in David's army</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam23:13-2Sam23:23\">2SA 23:13–23:23</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr11:15-1Chr11:25\">1CH 11:15–11:25</a> <em>the three mighty men among David's chiefs</em></p>\n<h3>Three annual festivals</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:14\">EXO 23:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:17\">EXO 23:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:23-Exod34:24\">EXO 34:23–34:24</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut16:16\">DEU 16:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs9:25\">1KI 9:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr8:13\">2CH 8:13</a></p>\n<h2>Three and a half</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:25\">DAN 7:25</a></strong> <em>NIV footnote.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan12:7\">DAN 12:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev11:2\">REV 11:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev12:6\">REV 12:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev13:5\">REV 13:5</a></p>\n<h2>Four</h2>\n<h3>Four representing the complete created order</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev7:1\">REV 7:1</a></strong> <em>This symbol is probably based on the four points of the compass.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer49:36\">JER 49:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek37:9\">EZK 37:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:2\">DAN 7:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:31\">MAT 24:31</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:27\">MRK 13:27</a></p>\n<h3>Four living creatures</h3>\n<p>The four living creatures in Ezekiel and Revelation represent the whole animate creation glorifying God:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek1:5-Ezek1:10\">EZK 1:5–1:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev4:6-Rev4:7\">REV 4:6–4:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev5:6\">REV 5:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev5:8\">REV 5:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev14:3\">REV 14:3</a></p>\n<h3>Four kingdoms</h3>\n<p>Human history before the coming of God's kingdom is spanned by four great human kingdoms, often understood to refer to the empires of Babylon, Persia, Greece and Rome:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:39-Dan2:40\">DAN 2:39–2:40</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:17\">DAN 7:17</a></p>\n<h2>Five</h2>\n<h3>Fives in Jesus Christ's teaching</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:2\">MAT 25:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:15-Matt25:20\">MAT 25:15–25:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:6\">LUK 12:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:52\">LUK 12:52</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:19\">LUK 14:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke16:28\">LUK 16:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:18-Luke19:19\">LUK 19:18–19:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:18\">JHN 4:18</a></p>\n<h3>Five loaves</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam21:3\">1SA 21:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:17-Matt14:19\">MAT 14:17–14:19</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:38-Mark6:41\">MRK 6:38–6:41</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:13-Luke9:16\">LUK 9:13–9:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:8-John6:13\">JHN 6:8–6:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:9\">MAT 16:9</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:19\">MRK 8:19</a></p>",
